<div class="main-container">
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">
        <span class="tag">RGUKT-AP ACADEMIC PORTAL</span>
        <h1 style="font-size: 2.8rem; margin-top: 10px;">The SGPA Master Guide</h1>
        <p>Expert Breakdown for Engineering Students (AIML, CSE, ECE & More)</p>
    </div>

    <section>
        <h2><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> SGPA Calculation Formula</h2>
        <div class="formula-card">
            <div style="text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px;">
                    SGPA = (Sum of Credit Points) ÷ (Total Credits)
                </p>
                <div style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2); padding-top: 15px; display: inline-block;">
                    <p><strong>Credit Points</strong> = Grade Point × Credits for that subject</p>
                    <p><strong>Total Credits</strong> = Sum of credits of all subjects in that semester</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2><i class="fas fa-route"></i> Step-by-Step Calculation Process</h2>
        <div class="step-grid">
            <div class="step-item"><span class="step-num">1</span> List all subjects, credits, and grades obtained.</div>
            <div class="step-item"><span class="step-num">2</span> Convert grades to points (e.g., EX=10, A=9).</div>
            <div class="step-item"><span class="step-num">3</span> Calculate Credit Points (Grade Point × Credits).</div>
            <div class="step-item"><span class="step-num">4</span> Sum all individual Credit Points.</div>
            <div class="step-item"><span class="step-num">5</span> Sum all the credits taken in the semester.</div>
            <div class="step-item"><span class="step-num">6</span> Divide total points by total credits for SGPA.</div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom: 50px;">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-flask"></i> Practical Example: AIML E1 Semester 1</h2>
        <p>A typical semester load for an Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning student:</p>
        <table class="example-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Subject</th>
                    <th>Credits</th>
                    <th>Grade</th>
                    <th>Grade Point</th>
                    <th>Credit Points</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Linear Algebra</td><td>4</td><td>A</td><td>9</td><td>36</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Python for AI</td><td>4</td><td>EX</td><td>10</td><td>40</td></tr>
                <tr><td>English for Comm.</td><td>2</td><td>B</td><td>8</td><td>16</td></tr>
                <tr><td>AI Ethics (Lab)</td><td>1.5</td><td>EX</td><td>10</td><td>15</td></tr>
                <tr style="background: #f0fdf4; font-weight: 700;">
                    <td>TOTAL</td><td>11.5</td><td>-</td><td>-</td><td>107</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <div style="margin-top: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--secondary);">
            Calculation: 107 ÷ 11.5 = <span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">9.30 SGPA</span>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom: 50px;">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-rocket"></i> 10 Tips to Improve Your SGPA</h2>
        <div class="tip-grid">
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Focus on 4-credit subjects first; they impact GPA the most.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Never lose internal marks (Mid-exams/Assignments).</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Aim for "EX" in Lab subjects; they are high-scoring.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Maintain at least 80% attendance for better concept clarity.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Solve previous 3 years' RGUKT question papers.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Study consistently; 2 hours daily beats a 12-hour cram.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Use the "Grade Improvement" exams if you hit a 'D' or 'E'.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Join peer study groups for difficult subjects like Maths/Physics.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Clarify doubts with faculty before the "Pre-Final" week.</div>
            <div class="tip-box"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Keep a healthy sleep schedule; a fresh mind scores higher.</div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="faq-card" style="background: #fff; padding: 25px; border-radius: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">
            <strong>Q1: What if I have a backlog (failed subject)?</strong>
            <p>Answer: Failed subjects (Grade F) get 0 grade points, which will lower your SGPA. You'll need to clear the backlog in subsequent semesters. The improved grade will be considered for CGPA calculation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-card" style="background: #fff; padding: 25px; border-radius: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">
            <strong>Q2: How is SGPA different from CGPA?</strong>
            <p>Answer: SGPA measures performance for ONE semester, while CGPA (Cumulative GPA) is the average of all semesters combined. CGPA = Total Credit Points of All Semesters ÷ Total Credits of All Semesters.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-card" style="background: #fff; padding: 25px; border-radius: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">
            <strong>Q3: Can SGPA be greater than 10?</strong>
            <p>Answer: No. Since the maximum grade point is 10 (EX grade), the maximum possible SGPA is also 10.00.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-card" style="background: #fff; padding: 25px; border-radius: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">
            <strong>Q4: Do all subjects have equal credits?</strong>
            <p>Answer: No. Theory subjects typically have 3-4 credits, lab subjects have 1.5-2 credits, and some subjects may have different credit values based on contact hours.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 40px; color: #64748b; font-size: 0.85rem;">
        <p>Keywords: SGPA Calculator, RGUKT Education, Math for Engineers, CGPA Percentage</p>
    </div>
